# Party HUD Feature Notes

## Accessibility
- Should be accessible via the Token Layer menu ([TokenLayer API](https://foundryvtt.com/api/classes/foundry.canvas.layers.TokenLayer.html))
  - Add a menu item in the token layer controls

## UI Structure
- Should utilize tabs ([Tabs API](https://foundryvtt.com/api/classes/foundry.applications.ux.Tabs.html))
  - **Tab 1: Party Status**
    - Hit points
    - AC
    - Conditions ([Active Effect Guide](https://github.com/foundryvtt/dnd5e/wiki/Active-Effect-Guide))
    - Speed
    - Death Save status
    - Spell slots used/total
  - **Tab 2: Loot Transfer**
    - Get info on Item Piles module to supplement
  - **Tab 3: Marching Order**
    - A grid where players can place their tokens in the order they want to move
  - **Tab 4: Inventory**
    - Each character's inventory (each PC should be collapsible)
    - Section for unclaimed items (everyone can pull items from loot piles onto character token/portraits)
    - Button to auto-distribute money to the party
  - **Tab 5: Party Magic Item & Wealth Tracker**
    - Pull info from the actor sheet of each character
    - Organize by rarity based on guidelines, showing which item and who owns it
    - Add up total party wealth and compare to game rules

## Functional Requirements
- Needs to update in real-time
- Should be able to pull tokens from this interface onto the canvas
- Should use tool-tips wherever possible ([TooltipManager API](https://foundryvtt.com/api/classes/foundry.helpers.interaction.TooltipManager.html))
- Should be resizable and movable
- Should be able to be hidden and shown
- Should be able to be locked and unlocked

## Visual Interface Options
- [ApplicationV2](https://foundryvtt.com/api/classes/foundry.applications.ApplicationV2.html)
- [HUD](https://foundryvtt.com/api/classes/foundry.applications.HUD.html)
- [Dialog](https://foundryvtt.com/api/classes/foundry.applications.Dialog.html)
- [Tabbed Application](https://foundryvtt.com/api/classes/foundry.applications.ux.TabbedApplication.html)
- [DocumentSheetV2](https://foundryvtt.com/api/classes/foundry.applications.api.DocumentSheetV2.html)

## Reference
- Secondary Reference: the DND5E system module ([DND5E Wiki](https://github.com/foundryvtt/dnd5e/wiki))
